Title : College bishop
Text : {{Distinguish|Bishop College}}
In the early days of the [[Scottish Episcopal Church]], '''college bishops''' were men who were [[Bishop#Ordination of Catholic, Orthodox and Anglican bishops|consecrated]] bishops in order to maintain [[apostolic succession]] but (extraordinarily) not appointed to any [[episcopal see]]. Fourteen such men were consecrated, eight of whom were later appointed to Scottish sees.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Ceey5RQHgHoC&pg=PA515 Bertie, David (ed.) Scottish Episcopal Clergy, 1689–2000: Chapter – College Bishops] p. 515 (Google Books; accessed 2 May 2014)</ref>

